an-Gudhinma \n|lc2= wrw |ld2=Gugu Warra \n|aiatsis=Y195\n|aiatsisname=Rimanggudinhma\n|aiatsis2=Y80\n|aiatsisname2=Gugu Warra\n|aiatsis3=Y66\n|aiatsisname3=Wurangung \n|glotto=mbar1253\n|glottoname=Rimanggudhinma \n|glotto2=gugu1256\n|glottoname2=Roth's Gugu Warra\n}}\n\n'''Mbariman-Gudhinma''' (Rimang-Gudinhma, Parimankutinma), one of several languages labeled '''Gugu Warra''' (Kuku-Wara) 'bad/unintelligible speech' as opposed to [[Gugu Mini]] 'good/intelligible speech',<ref name=\"AIATSIS\" /> is an extinct [[dialect cluster]] of [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Pama\u2013Nyungan languages|Paman}}\n\n[[Category:Paman languages]]\n[[Category:Extinct languages of Queensland]]\n[[Category:Languages extinct in the 2000s]]\n\n\n{{IndigenousAustralian-lang-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toLama Lama(link changed toLama Lama people) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mbariman-Gudhinma_language"}
{"title_page": "8373 Stephengould", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox planet\n| minorplanet = yes\n| background = #D6D6D6\n| name = Stephengould\n| image = \n| caption = \n| discovery_ref = <ref name=\"MPC\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cfa.harvard.edu/iau/lists/NumberedMPs005001.html | title=Discovery Circumstances: Numbered Minor Planets (5001)\u2013(10000) | accessdate=7 December 2008  | publisher=IAU: Minor Planet Center }}</ref>\n| discoverer = {{Ubl\n | [[Carolyn S. Shoemaker]]\n | [[Eugene Merle Shoemaker]]\n }}\n| discovery_site = [[Palomar Observatory|Palomar]]\n| discovered = 1 January 1992\n| mpc_name = (8373) Stephengould\n| alt_names = 1992 AB\n| named_after = [[Stephen Jay Gould]]\n| mp_category = {{Hlist\n | [[main-belt]]\n | {{small|([[Kirkwood gap|outer]])}}&thinsp;<ref name=\"jpldata\" />\n | [[Orbital resonance|2:1 res.]]&thinsp;<ref name=\"Roig-2002\" />\n }}\n| orbit_ref = <ref>{{cite web | url=https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.0&n=8373 | title=(8373) Stephengould | accessdate=10 December 2008 | work=AstDyS | publisher=[[University of Pisa]] | location=Italy | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110526223143/http://hamilton.dm.unipi.it/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.0&n=8373 | archive-date=26 May 2011 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"jpldata\">{{Cite web |url=https://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi?sstr=8373;cad=1 |title=8373 Stephengould (1992 AB) |work=[[JPL Small-Body Database]] |publisher=[[NASA]]/[[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]] |access-date=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n| epoch = 13 January 2016 ([[Julian day|JD]]&nbsp;2457400.5)\n| aphelion = {{Convert|5.09996|AU|Gm|abbr=on|lk=on}}\n| perihelion = {{Convert|1.45970|AU|Gm|abbr=on}}\n| semimajor = {{Convert|3.27983|AU|Gm|abbr=on}}\n| eccentricity = 0.554947\n| period = 5.94&nbsp;[[Julian year (astronomy)|yr]] (2169.6&nbsp;[[Julian year (astronomy)|d]])\n| inclination = 40.7923\u00b0\n| asc_node = 88.8722\u00b0\n| mean_anomaly = 358.004[[Degree (angle)|\u00b0]]\n| arg_peri = 55.5019\u00b0\n| satellites = 1\n| dimensions = \n| albedo = \n| spectral_type = \n| abs_magnitude = 14.0\n| mean_motion = {{Deg2DMS|0.165931|sup=ms}} / day\n| rotation = {{Convert|4.435|h|d|abbr=on|lk=on}}\n| observation_arc = 8844 days (24.21&nbsp;yr)\n| uncertainty = 0\n| jupiter_moid = {{Convert|1.4741|AU|Gm|abbr=on}}\n| tisserand = 2.587\n}}\n'''8373 Stephengould''' (1992 AB) is an [[Outer asteroid belt|outer main-belt]] [[binary asteroid]]<ref name=binary /> discovered on 1 January 1992 by [[Carolyn S. Shoemaker]] and [[Eugene Merle Shoemaker]] at [[Palomar Observatory]].<ref name=\"MPC\"/> The asteroid was named after the [[Harvard]] paleontologist [[Stephen Jay Gould]]. The asteroid has a very high inclination, having the second highest inclination of any of the first 10,000 discovered asteroids in the asteroid belt, after [[2938 Hopi]].\n\n''Stephengould'' is one of few strongly unstable asteroids located near the 2:1 [[Orbital resonance|mean motion resonance]] with the gas giant [[Jupiter]], that corresponds to one of the prominent [[Kirkwood gaps]] in the asteroid belt.<ref name=\"Roig-2002\" />\n\nThe asteroid has a moon orbiting it, discovered in 2010 with an orbital period of 1 day, 10 hours, and 9 minutes.<ref name=binary/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of minor planets]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=binary>{{cite web\n  |last1=Johnston\n  |first1=Robert\n  |title=(8373) Stephengould\n  |url=http://www.johnstonsarchive.net/astro/astmoons/am-08373.html\n  |website=johnstonsarchive.net\n  |accessdate=29 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Roig-2002\">{{Cite journal\n  |first1     = F. |last1 = Roig\n  |first2     = D. |last2 = Nesvorn\u00fd\n  |first3     = S. |last3 = Ferraz-Mello\n  |date       = September 2002\n  |title      = Asteroids in the 2 : 1 resonance with Jupiter: dynamics and size distribution [ Erratum: 2002MNRAS.336.1391R ]\n  |url        = http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/bib_query?bibcode=2002MNRAS.335..417R